    <body>
      <trans-unit id="8629" identifier="6b3d3e51d727c2bd4134175fae99d104">
        <source>Make a variable called “number of dots” and change its value by using an
operator (multiplying it by 2 before displaying it on the screen each time).</source>
        <target>crwdns8629:0crwdne8629:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8630" identifier="c74a3cf035dbc17eb8e0e38baa62d207">
        <source>You can find “make a new variable” under “data” script to create a new
variable.</source>
        <target>crwdns8630:0crwdne8630:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8631" identifier="1518b5d580f4bc7403d05689fdfd8688">
        <source>Make sure your variable name is as descriptive as possible.</source>
        <target>crwdns8631:0crwdne8631:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8632" identifier="b9402ce57598fabacf36a36c872147fa">
        <source>Use the &lt;code&gt;scratch:set [number of dots v] to [1]&lt;/code&gt; block to set the value of
your new variable.</source>
        <target>crwdns8632:0[1]crwdne8632:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8633" identifier="407d2ed6ca7ba6f2ad1f4a840ec3973e">
        <source>Use the &lt;code&gt;scratch:() * ()&lt;/code&gt; operation under “Operators” to double the value of
your variable.</source>
        <target>crwdns8633:0crwdne8633:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8634" identifier="fe2a6470783cb0ce27fa65a79e0d2958">
        <source>Display the value of your variable on the screen by replacing
“Hello” in your &lt;code&gt;scratch:say [Hello] for (2) secs&lt;/code&gt; block with your new
variable.</source>
        <target>crwdns8634:0[Hello]crwdne8634:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
